      <div class="article-teaser">
        <p>The Ultra Low Emission Zone (ULEZ) and Low Emission Zone (LEZ) operate 24 hours a day, every day of the year, including weekends and public and bank holidays.</p>
        
      </div>
    
    
      <p>Charging days run from midnight to midnight. So if you drive within the zones between 23:30 and 01:00 the next day, you need to pay for 2 days.</p>

<p>The ULEZ covers central London, in the&nbsp;same area as the Congestion Charge. The LEZ operates across most of Greater London.</p>

<p>The charges only need to be paid if you drive your vehicle within the zone. Parked vehicles are not subject to any charges.</p>

<p>As well as ULEZ and LEZ charges, you may also need to pay the Congestion Charge. The Congestion Charge applies from 07:00 to 18:00 Monday to Friday, excluding public and bank holidays. If you drive within the Congestion Charge zone during these times you need to pay the Congestion Charge, even if you meet the ULEZ and/or LEZ emissions standards or have paid those daily charges.</p>

<p>Use the links below to find out if your vehicle is affected by the ULEZ and/or LEZ and if your journey takes you into the zone.</p>
      
           
